WEBVTT

STYLE
::cue(c.color9CD5FF) { color: #9CD5FF; }
::cue(c.colora8c7fa) { color: #a8c7fa; }

1
00:00:01.000 --> 00:00:07.000 line:5% align:middle
<b><c.color9CD5FF>One Pace Premium</c></b>
Keep the project alive: <c.colora8c7fa>ko-fi.com/not6ip</c>

2
00:00:12.900 --> 00:00:14.630
Inherited will...

3
00:00:14.630 --> 00:00:17.540
the tides of time,
and humanity's dreams...

4
00:00:17.540 --> 00:00:20.370
They cannot be stopped.

5
00:00:20.370 --> 00:00:23.480
As long as people seek freedom,

6
00:00:23.480 --> 00:00:26.110
these things will never cease to be.

7
00:00:34.820 --> 00:00:41.040
I only believe in the future -- I don't care if anyone laughs

8
00:00:41.080 --> 00:00:46.560
That racing passion makes you shine

9
00:00:46.580 --> 00:00:52.100
It's too bright, but I want to gaze at it

10
00:00:52.440 --> 00:00:56.080
I sense "aesthetics" somewhere

11
00:00:59.440 --> 00:01:02.700
I follow, follow in the footsteps

12
00:01:02.700 --> 00:01:05.990
of a dream that resembles no one

13
00:01:05.990 --> 00:01:09.220
Until I dramatically get it

14
00:01:18.080 --> 00:01:21.120
I'm going to catch, catch the shape

15
00:01:21.220 --> 00:01:24.200
of a dream no one can see

16
00:01:24.480 --> 00:01:30.220
I'm going to go with you, so passionate feelings

17
00:01:30.460 --> 00:01:33.580
I don't really need everything to add up

18
00:01:33.560 --> 00:01:36.750
Rather than run-of-the-mill daily life,

19
00:01:36.760 --> 00:01:40.350
run for paradise instead

20
00:01:49.960 --> 00:01:54.920
<b>Tin Plate Wapol</b>

21
00:01:55.260 --> 00:02:00.430
Guys! Someday, I will go to Elbaph!
To the village of warriors!

22
00:02:00.430 --> 00:02:01.890
Yeah! Okay!

23
00:02:02.270 --> 00:02:06.150
♪ Gi-Gi-Giants! Gia-Giants! ♪

24
00:02:06.150 --> 00:02:10.070
♪ Elbaph-baph! Elbaph-baph! ♪

25
00:02:10.070 --> 00:02:13.860
♪ Everyone's huge
'cause they're giants! ♪

26
00:02:13.860 --> 00:02:17.410
♪ They're huge! They're huge!
They're huge! ♪

27
00:02:17.410 --> 00:02:19.160
They sure are lively today...

28
00:02:21.580 --> 00:02:22.410
Hey!

29
00:02:26.330 --> 00:02:29.710
Suddenly, I'm pretty worn out
after all that's happened...

30
00:02:29.710 --> 00:02:31.090
Vivi...

31
00:02:31.090 --> 00:02:33.550
Could you keep an eye
on the needle for me?

32
00:02:33.550 --> 00:02:34.630
Sure.

33
00:02:38.350 --> 00:02:41.720
Now you can finally...
return to Alabasta.

34
00:02:41.720 --> 00:02:46.650
That is, assuming we can
avoid trouble along the way.

35
00:02:47.270 --> 00:02:50.650
Yes. It's time I returned!

36
00:02:50.650 --> 00:02:53.190
After all, I am...

37
00:02:53.570 --> 00:02:56.660
...the only one who can
save the kingdom, Princess!

38
00:02:56.660 --> 00:03:01.990
The king—your father—no longer
holds sway over his people.

39
00:03:01.990 --> 00:03:06.290
Our only hope to stem
the tide of rebellion is for the country

40
00:03:06.290 --> 00:03:08.630
to hear the truth directly from you.

41
00:03:09.380 --> 00:03:12.550
So, no matter the cost,
you must not die!

42
00:03:12.550 --> 00:03:15.550
If it means you survive,
then sacrifice those closest to you

43
00:03:15.550 --> 00:03:18.140
or betray them to your enemies!

44
00:03:18.140 --> 00:03:19.470
It will be agony!

45
00:03:19.970 --> 00:03:21.350
Princess Vivi!

46
00:03:21.350 --> 00:03:23.930
Are you resolved to stay alive?

47
00:03:26.850 --> 00:03:29.810
I will stay alive
and return to Alabasta.

48
00:03:30.400 --> 00:03:33.570
No need to push
yourself so hard, Vivi.

49
00:03:35.110 --> 00:03:36.070
You have me!

50
00:03:37.450 --> 00:03:40.950
Today's sweets will put you
right at ease. Petit fours?

51
00:03:40.950 --> 00:03:43.290
And to drink, would you
like coffee or tea?

52
00:03:44.540 --> 00:03:45.750
Sanji!

53
00:03:48.750 --> 00:03:50.170
Yours is in the kitchen!

54
00:03:50.170 --> 00:03:52.340
– Alright!
– Alright!

55
00:03:53.170 --> 00:03:55.010
I got there first!

56
00:03:55.670 --> 00:03:57.470
2,603...

57
00:03:57.880 --> 00:03:59.390
2,604...

58
00:04:02.600 --> 00:04:05.520
If only I'd been able
to cut through that wax...

59
00:04:07.100 --> 00:04:09.730
we would've escaped so much sooner.

60
00:04:12.480 --> 00:04:13.780
I'm weak...

61
00:04:15.860 --> 00:04:17.740
I need to get stronger...

62
00:04:18.860 --> 00:04:22.990
and get to where I can
cut through stuff like that with ease!

63
00:04:26.950 --> 00:04:28.160
Vivi...

64
00:04:28.160 --> 00:04:30.040
Sorry. I think I'm gonna...

65
00:04:36.710 --> 00:04:37.920
go lie down.

66
00:04:39.130 --> 00:04:40.720
No problem, Nami!

67
00:04:40.720 --> 00:04:42.640
I'll keep an eye on our heading.

68
00:04:42.640 --> 00:04:44.260
You should get some rest.

69
00:04:50.140 --> 00:04:51.230
Are you all right?!

70
00:04:51.850 --> 00:04:53.610
Everyone, come here! It's urgent!

71
00:04:55.650 --> 00:04:57.530
Huh? What's up, Vivi?

72
00:04:57.530 --> 00:04:58.780
Nami has a terrible fever!

73
00:04:59.150 --> 00:05:01.360
Say what?! Nami has a what?!

74
00:05:19.420 --> 00:05:22.390
Mr. 2 Bon Kurei!

75
00:05:20.840 --> 00:05:24.510
<b>Sandy Island
Kingdom of Alabasta</b>

76
00:05:22.390 --> 00:05:24.510
The Swanda is ready to set sail!

77
00:05:25.100 --> 00:05:29.180
Okay, okay! Dial it down a notch!

78
00:05:29.680 --> 00:05:33.190
Honestly! What does any of this
have to do with me?!

79
00:05:33.190 --> 00:05:36.020
Mr. 3 is a waste of space!
You guys go finish him off!

80
00:05:36.020 --> 00:05:37.780
W-We can't!

81
00:05:37.780 --> 00:05:40.150
Even all of us together
wouldn't stand a chance!

82
00:05:40.150 --> 00:05:42.860
P-Please! It's the boss' orders!

83
00:05:42.860 --> 00:05:45.410
Un, deux, trois...

84
00:05:45.910 --> 00:05:50.870
"Bon Kurei"

85
00:05:46.280 --> 00:05:48.330
What's "four" again?

86
00:05:52.330 --> 00:05:54.790
Zero baby is so high maintenance...

87
00:05:57.550 --> 00:05:59.550
Is Nami gonna die?

88
00:05:59.550 --> 00:06:01.510
Is she, Vivi?

89
00:06:01.510 --> 00:06:03.050
It's most likely the climate.

90
00:06:03.050 --> 00:06:07.260
Illness caused by abnormal weather
is a well-known obstacle

91
00:06:07.260 --> 00:06:09.020
for those new to the Grand Line.

92
00:06:10.140 --> 00:06:16.150
There are countless stories
of the toughest, most infamous pirates

93
00:06:16.150 --> 00:06:17.690
suddenly dying from it.

94
00:06:18.480 --> 00:06:21.570
If left untreated,
even the slightest chill can be fatal.

95
00:06:22.950 --> 00:06:25.200
Nami!

96
00:06:26.070 --> 00:06:29.620
Does someone on the ship have
any kind of medical training?

97
00:06:33.620 --> 00:06:38.340
Well, she'll feel better once
she eats some meat! Right, Sanji?

98
00:06:38.340 --> 00:06:42.340
Y'know, I can think of a few meals
meant to nurse sick people.

99
00:06:42.340 --> 00:06:46.470
But nursing isn't my expertise,
so there's no telling if it would help.

100
00:06:47.350 --> 00:06:49.640
Even so, I put 100 times more care...

101
00:06:50.310 --> 00:06:55.390
into Nami and Vivi's meals
than I do yours.

102
00:06:55.850 --> 00:06:59.520
To balance their diet, I only serve them
fresh meat and vegetables.

103
00:06:59.520 --> 00:07:00.940
And I give the rotting stuff...

104
00:07:01.440 --> 00:07:02.610
to you guys.

105
00:07:02.610 --> 00:07:03.440
Hey, now!

106
00:07:03.440 --> 00:07:05.450
It tastes great, though!

107
00:07:07.200 --> 00:07:10.700
My point is, as long as
I'm this ship's cook,

108
00:07:10.700 --> 00:07:14.960
I will always guarantee
you get a balanced diet.

109
00:07:15.330 --> 00:07:16.290
But...

110
00:07:16.960 --> 00:07:20.090
sick people require specific meals.

111
00:07:20.090 --> 00:07:22.590
What does she need,
and for which symptoms?

112
00:07:22.590 --> 00:07:24.800
I can't make that call.

113
00:07:25.300 --> 00:07:27.430
Then feed her everything!

114
00:07:27.930 --> 00:07:31.890
Going overboard like that
is bound to make her sicker!

115
00:07:33.520 --> 00:07:36.480
I-It's at 40 degrees?!
Her fever's gone up!

116
00:07:36.850 --> 00:07:40.060
There are doctors in Alabasta, right?!

117
00:07:40.060 --> 00:07:41.690
How long till we arrive, Vivi?

118
00:07:42.900 --> 00:07:44.490
A week maybe...

119
00:07:44.490 --> 00:07:46.450
but it might be too late by then.

120
00:07:47.200 --> 00:07:49.120
Is being sick that bad?

121
00:07:49.490 --> 00:07:51.830
– Dunno. Never been sick.
– Dunno. Never been sick.

122
00:07:51.830 --> 00:07:54.450
Who in the world are you guys?!

123
00:07:54.950 --> 00:07:56.580
Of course it's bad!

124
00:07:56.580 --> 00:07:59.920
Fevers of 40 degrees
don't happen every day!

125
00:08:00.420 --> 00:08:03.630
Her life may very well be at stake.

126
00:08:05.210 --> 00:08:10.390
– Nami's gonna die?!
– Don't die, Nami!

127
00:08:10.390 --> 00:08:12.300
Settle down! Be quiet!

128
00:08:12.300 --> 00:08:15.890
Let's find a doctor to help Nami!

129
00:08:16.560 --> 00:08:18.440
Okay! Just calm down!

130
00:08:18.440 --> 00:08:19.980
You'll make her worse!

131
00:08:19.980 --> 00:08:20.810
No...

132
00:08:21.770 --> 00:08:22.400
Nami?

133
00:08:23.070 --> 00:08:24.280
No...

134
00:08:25.820 --> 00:08:26.820
Nami?

135
00:08:26.820 --> 00:08:28.450
Oh! She's all better!

136
00:08:28.450 --> 00:08:29.280
Get real!

137
00:08:31.280 --> 00:08:33.780
In my desk drawer...

138
00:08:33.780 --> 00:08:35.620
there's a newspaper.

139
00:08:40.210 --> 00:08:43.170
No change in course...

140
00:08:43.920 --> 00:08:45.880
N-No!

141
00:08:46.260 --> 00:08:47.760
This can't be!

142
00:08:47.760 --> 00:08:50.010
Hey. What is it?

143
00:08:50.010 --> 00:08:51.970
Is it about Alabasta, Vivi?

144
00:08:52.720 --> 00:08:57.310
My kingdom just saw 300,000 of
the Royal Army defect to the Rebellion.

145
00:09:00.350 --> 00:09:03.360
It all started as a cold war

146
00:09:03.360 --> 00:09:07.030
with the 600,000 Royal Army soldiers
deterring the 400,000 rebels.

147
00:09:07.030 --> 00:09:08.990
But this changes everything!

148
00:09:11.280 --> 00:09:14.870
The tensions in Alabasta are
only going to intensify from here on.

149
00:09:15.490 --> 00:09:17.330
That paper's from three days ago.

150
00:09:18.200 --> 00:09:19.620
I'm sorry...

151
00:09:19.620 --> 00:09:22.670
We can only go so fast.

152
00:09:22.670 --> 00:09:24.790
I thought if you saw this
you'd only worry...

153
00:09:25.590 --> 00:09:27.300
Understand, Luffy?

154
00:09:28.670 --> 00:09:30.970
Things look pretty bad!

155
00:09:30.970 --> 00:09:32.800
Whew, you got the gist of it.

156
00:09:32.800 --> 00:09:35.260
But you still need to see a doctor!

157
00:09:35.680 --> 00:09:38.680
I'm fine... That thermometer
must be broken.

158
00:09:38.680 --> 00:09:41.270
Nobody gets
a temperature of 40 degrees...

159
00:09:41.850 --> 00:09:43.770
It's most likely sunstroke.

160
00:09:44.230 --> 00:09:47.150
I don't need a doctor.
I'll get better on my own.

161
00:09:47.780 --> 00:09:51.110
For now, let's head
straight for Alabasta as planned!

162
00:09:53.110 --> 00:09:55.490
Thanks for worrying about me.

163
00:10:01.290 --> 00:10:03.920
Oh! She's better now?

164
00:10:03.920 --> 00:10:05.710
Don't be stupid. It's just a front.

165
00:10:06.290 --> 00:10:10.210
At this rate, blood will flow
through the kingdom's streets.

166
00:10:10.210 --> 00:10:11.470
It'll be an all-out war.

167
00:10:11.840 --> 00:10:16.350
If I don't prevent that,
the Kingdom of Alabasta will be finished.

168
00:10:16.970 --> 00:10:19.390
Crocodile will take over!

169
00:10:19.930 --> 00:10:23.230
It's not enough...
to simply get back alive!

170
00:10:23.230 --> 00:10:24.850
I must expedite my return!

171
00:10:25.600 --> 00:10:30.360
A moment wasted means a million citizens
will senselessly kill each other!

172
00:10:30.360 --> 00:10:32.990
There's a million people?!

173
00:10:32.990 --> 00:10:36.450
What an immense burden
you're carrying, Vivi.

174
00:10:47.670 --> 00:10:50.380
C'mon! Were you even
paying attention up here?!

175
00:10:50.380 --> 00:10:51.550
Whad'ya mean?

176
00:10:51.550 --> 00:10:53.550
The ship's going straight.

177
00:10:53.550 --> 00:10:55.800
Yeah, straight at a right angle!

178
00:10:55.800 --> 00:10:57.850
You need to watch the needle!

179
00:10:57.850 --> 00:11:01.720
That wasn't necessary.
I was watching that big cloud there.

180
00:11:01.720 --> 00:11:04.190
Clouds move and change shape!

181
00:11:04.810 --> 00:11:07.310
Oh, man, my head's killing me...

182
00:11:07.310 --> 00:11:09.570
So then leave this to me
and go to bed!

183
00:11:09.570 --> 00:11:12.820
I'm here because
I can't leave this to you!

184
00:11:14.650 --> 00:11:16.610
The air's different.

185
00:11:16.610 --> 00:11:19.740
The air? The weather's been
nice this whole time.

186
00:11:19.740 --> 00:11:22.080
Forget it! Just get the others!

187
00:11:22.080 --> 00:11:24.790
Hey! Get out here, you guys!
We've got work to do!

188
00:11:25.410 --> 00:11:26.920
– What?
– Huh?

189
00:11:27.790 --> 00:11:29.170
Huh?

190
00:11:29.170 --> 00:11:31.960
Hard to feel motivated
when it's you giving the orders.

191
00:11:32.420 --> 00:11:33.960
Just shut up and move!

192
00:11:33.960 --> 00:11:36.430
Hoist the sails
and catch the wind aport!

193
00:11:36.800 --> 00:11:38.510
Everything okay, Nami?

194
00:11:38.510 --> 00:11:40.640
The waves are quiet,
and the weather's nice.

195
00:11:41.470 --> 00:11:42.310
The wind...

196
00:11:43.310 --> 00:11:44.350
The wind?

197
00:11:44.730 --> 00:11:48.100
The wind is picking up
and heading directly toward us.

198
00:11:48.100 --> 00:11:49.560
I think th–

199
00:11:49.560 --> 00:11:50.520
What?

200
00:11:51.320 --> 00:11:52.320
Hot!

201
00:11:52.320 --> 00:11:55.440
You're burning up! Yeah,
stay inside until we find a doctor!

202
00:11:55.440 --> 00:11:57.070
Mind your own business!

203
00:11:57.070 --> 00:11:58.820
This is my normal temperature!

204
00:11:58.820 --> 00:12:00.740
Quit being dumb and man the ropes!

205
00:12:01.080 --> 00:12:06.210
Nami, I get that this is
for Vivi's sake, but if you overdo it...

206
00:12:06.870 --> 00:12:08.420
I told you, I'm fine!

207
00:12:10.540 --> 00:12:13.130
C'mon, Nami! You really ought to–

208
00:12:13.130 --> 00:12:15.630
Just hurry it up and turn the ship!

209
00:12:23.510 --> 00:12:24.220
But...

210
00:12:25.390 --> 00:12:27.520
what could it be?

211
00:12:27.520 --> 00:12:30.730
This is a bit different from a storm.

212
00:12:57.510 --> 00:13:01.180
I need to hurry... back to Alabasta.

213
00:13:04.560 --> 00:13:05.970
Everyone, I need a favor!

214
00:13:07.770 --> 00:13:11.770
As a passenger on your ship,
I know I have no right to ask this,

215
00:13:11.770 --> 00:13:15.270
but my homeland is
on the brink of disaster.

216
00:13:15.270 --> 00:13:16.980
So we need to expedite our trip!

217
00:13:16.980 --> 00:13:19.450
We can't waste even a single minute!

218
00:13:19.450 --> 00:13:23.910
You must take me to Alabasta
at this ship's top speed!

219
00:13:25.200 --> 00:13:27.830
Of course!
That's what we promised!

220
00:13:31.710 --> 00:13:35.420
So let's find an island
with a doctor right away!

221
00:13:35.790 --> 00:13:40.420
The sooner we cure Nami,
the sooner we get to Alabasta!

222
00:13:40.420 --> 00:13:42.970
That's this ship's top speed, right?!

223
00:13:43.470 --> 00:13:46.470
Yeah! We can't go
any faster than that!

224
00:13:46.850 --> 00:13:48.350
Are you sure?

225
00:13:48.350 --> 00:13:52.350
Shouldn't a princess be more worried
about her one million citizens?

226
00:13:52.770 --> 00:13:56.770
You're right! All the more reason
to hurry and cure Nami!

227
00:13:57.190 --> 00:14:00.740
Well said, Vivi! I've fallen
for you all over again!

228
00:14:01.110 --> 00:14:02.780
You've got spirit.

229
00:14:03.450 --> 00:14:04.780
Thanks...

230
00:14:05.700 --> 00:14:07.450
Don't overexert yourself, Nami!

231
00:14:10.370 --> 00:14:13.620
Sorry, Vivi. Y'know...

232
00:14:13.620 --> 00:14:15.130
I might be... in trouble.

233
00:14:15.130 --> 00:14:16.500
Nami! Hang in there!

234
00:14:16.920 --> 00:14:20.380
What the heck is that?!

235
00:14:20.380 --> 00:14:22.010
It's a cyclone!

236
00:14:22.010 --> 00:14:23.050
It's huge!

237
00:14:23.430 --> 00:14:26.050
W-Wait! That's the direction–

238
00:14:26.050 --> 00:14:29.060
That's the direction our ship
was just going!

239
00:14:29.060 --> 00:14:32.520
We would've hit it head-on
had we kept our original heading!

240
00:14:41.570 --> 00:14:42.860
Yikes!

241
00:14:42.860 --> 00:14:45.160
We just barely missed it!

242
00:14:45.530 --> 00:14:46.910
Incredible!

243
00:14:46.910 --> 00:14:50.790
Grand Line cyclones are said
to be impossible to predict!

244
00:14:50.790 --> 00:14:51.870
Yet, she...

245
00:14:52.750 --> 00:14:56.250
She doesn't predict weather
based on prevailing theory.

246
00:14:56.250 --> 00:14:59.340
It's almost as if she's detecting
the weather with her body!

247
00:14:59.840 --> 00:15:02.300
This navigator is one of a kind!

248
00:15:02.840 --> 00:15:05.260
Alright! Let's hurry, then!

249
00:15:05.930 --> 00:15:08.470
Let's go find us a doctor!

250
00:15:08.470 --> 00:15:09.470
– Yeah!
– Yeah!

251
00:15:20.690 --> 00:15:23.990
<b>The Next Day</b>

252
00:15:28.160 --> 00:15:31.950
What do we do, Vivi?!
Nami's fever won't break!

253
00:15:31.950 --> 00:15:34.960
Sanji! Karoo! I asked you
to stop freaking out!

254
00:15:40.340 --> 00:15:42.000
See any doctors?!

255
00:15:42.000 --> 00:15:43.840
You actually expect him to, moron?

256
00:15:48.090 --> 00:15:51.470
Hey, guys. Ever heard of people
who could stand on the ocean?

257
00:15:51.470 --> 00:15:53.720
Can people stand on the ocean?

258
00:15:53.720 --> 00:15:56.440
C'mon, Zoro.
Is this some kind of riddle?

259
00:15:56.850 --> 00:15:59.770
Then... what's that?

260
00:16:00.150 --> 00:16:01.400
What's what?

261
00:16:01.400 --> 00:16:02.610
Huh?

262
00:16:23.750 --> 00:16:25.760
Hi. It sure is chilly today.

263
00:16:27.930 --> 00:16:29.430
Yeah! It is chilly today!

264
00:16:29.430 --> 00:16:32.800
Y-Yeah! Chilly, chilly!
Today's very chilly!

265
00:16:32.800 --> 00:16:33.970
Really?

266
00:16:38.640 --> 00:16:40.100
Increase buoyancy!

267
00:16:40.560 --> 00:16:41.100
Yes, sir!

268
00:16:47.650 --> 00:16:49.450
What's that?! A watermelon?!

269
00:16:49.860 --> 00:16:50.990
Why are we shaking?!

270
00:16:50.990 --> 00:16:53.080
Steady the rudder!

271
00:16:53.080 --> 00:16:55.700
If anything happens
to Nami, I'll gut you all!

272
00:16:59.830 --> 00:17:03.000
This thing can't actually be... a ship?!

273
00:17:25.070 --> 00:17:26.400
Crap!

274
00:17:26.400 --> 00:17:28.320
A p-pirate ship!

275
00:17:28.320 --> 00:17:30.200
S-So cool!

276
00:17:30.860 --> 00:17:32.910
Just when we're in a hurry...

277
00:17:36.080 --> 00:17:42.370
Surprised?! It's our jumbo
submersible raid ship, the Bliking!

278
00:17:46.800 --> 00:17:48.590
Vivi! Take over!

279
00:17:48.590 --> 00:17:49.420
Okay!

280
00:17:50.090 --> 00:17:52.470
Hey! What's going on?!

281
00:18:06.060 --> 00:18:06.820
So?

282
00:18:07.610 --> 00:18:08.780
What's going on?

283
00:18:09.440 --> 00:18:11.490
The ship's under attack.

284
00:18:15.910 --> 00:18:21.580
Well, I had figured as much
from the looks of things.

285
00:18:23.210 --> 00:18:27.840
Are you really pirates?
This can't be right.

286
00:18:27.840 --> 00:18:29.840
Is it just the four of you?

287
00:18:31.260 --> 00:18:37.220
<b>"Tin Plate" Wapol
Bliking Pirates</b>

288
00:18:32.340 --> 00:18:34.340
I find it hard to believe...

289
00:18:34.340 --> 00:18:37.220
that a pirate group would only have four people.

290
00:18:41.350 --> 00:18:43.190
What is that guy?!

291
00:18:43.190 --> 00:18:44.900
He even ate the knife!

292
00:18:46.270 --> 00:18:48.270
Just watching hurts!

293
00:18:49.650 --> 00:18:52.400
Well, no matter.
First, a question for you.

294
00:18:53.360 --> 00:18:56.280
We want to go
to the Kingdom of Drum.

295
00:18:56.280 --> 00:19:00.290
Do you happen to have
an eternal pose or a log pose?

296
00:19:00.290 --> 00:19:05.080
Nope. Never even heard of the place.

297
00:19:05.080 --> 00:19:07.920
Hey, if that's everything,
then get outta here!

298
00:19:07.920 --> 00:19:09.420
We're in a hurry!

299
00:19:09.420 --> 00:19:12.420
We don't have time to mess with you!

300
00:19:14.010 --> 00:19:16.260
Don't rush life like that.

301
00:19:16.260 --> 00:19:18.100
So you don't have either one, oh well.

302
00:19:18.100 --> 00:19:20.970
In that case, I'll take
your treasure and your ship.

303
00:19:20.970 --> 00:19:21.890
What?!

304
00:19:21.890 --> 00:19:25.600
But first, I'm feeling a bit hungry!

305
00:19:30.690 --> 00:19:32.610
What is this guy?!

306
00:19:32.610 --> 00:19:34.110
Get your mouth off our ship!

307
00:19:34.110 --> 00:19:35.320
Hold it right there!

308
00:19:35.320 --> 00:19:37.570
The great Wapol is currently eating!

309
00:19:37.570 --> 00:19:38.320
Shut up!

310
00:19:38.320 --> 00:19:41.030
Damn that bastard! Fire!

311
00:19:42.370 --> 00:19:44.830
Should've done that from the start...

312
00:19:45.870 --> 00:19:47.710
Oh? We can have at 'em?

313
00:19:47.710 --> 00:19:49.670
No, wait! We can discuss this!

314
00:19:56.090 --> 00:19:58.180
Look what they started.

315
00:19:58.180 --> 00:20:00.600
They're fools rushing to their deaths!

316
00:20:00.600 --> 00:20:01.640
Gunfire?!

317
00:20:02.180 --> 00:20:05.020
Karoo! Watch Nami!
I'll be right back!

318
00:20:08.020 --> 00:20:10.730
Don't bite off
more than you can chew!

319
00:20:10.730 --> 00:20:11.820
Réception!

320
00:20:35.920 --> 00:20:37.130
All bark and no bite.

321
00:20:37.470 --> 00:20:39.840
W-Wapol, sir! These guys are...!

322
00:20:41.760 --> 00:20:43.390
Hey! Are you still eating it?!

323
00:20:43.390 --> 00:20:45.390
Say, this ship doesn't taste half bad.

324
00:20:45.390 --> 00:20:46.480
Hey, you!

325
00:20:46.480 --> 00:20:48.600
Fool! You're no match
for the great Wapol!

326
00:20:48.600 --> 00:20:51.350
His Munch-Munch Fruit power
will eat you whole!

327
00:20:51.350 --> 00:20:52.730
Luffy!

328
00:20:54.150 --> 00:20:55.400
Wh-What is this?!

329
00:20:56.030 --> 00:20:58.860
Oh, Vivi, is everything
okay with Nami?

330
00:20:58.860 --> 00:20:59.400
Huh?

331
00:21:02.870 --> 00:21:05.370
This guy's hard to chew on!

332
00:21:06.540 --> 00:21:08.580
Why, you!

333
00:21:09.580 --> 00:21:14.670
Go flying!

334
00:21:15.460 --> 00:21:17.630
Wapol...?

335
00:21:19.720 --> 00:21:22.970
Hey, this is really bad!
He sent the great Wapol flying!

336
00:21:22.970 --> 00:21:27.430
This is a disaster!
The great Wapol isn't able to swim!

337
00:21:27.430 --> 00:21:34.650
He will surely drown and perish in the sea
if he sinks before we can retrieve him!

338
00:21:34.650 --> 00:21:36.320
This isn't over, you!

339
00:21:36.320 --> 00:21:38.320
We'll make you pay for this!

340
00:21:38.320 --> 00:21:40.400
Remember us!

341
00:21:40.400 --> 00:21:42.320
You're gonna pay!

342
00:21:42.320 --> 00:21:45.660
Please, remember us!

343
00:21:45.660 --> 00:21:47.370
Please!

344
00:21:57.340 --> 00:22:01.340
J-Just now, what was all that?

345
00:22:01.340 --> 00:22:03.510
So, I guess his name is Wapol?

346
00:22:03.510 --> 00:22:06.220
Doesn't matter. Don't sweat it.

347
00:22:06.220 --> 00:22:07.970
He's a moron.

348
00:22:07.970 --> 00:22:09.770
Let's just forget about him.

349
00:22:17.190 --> 00:22:20.190
Where have I seen him before?

350
00:22:29.740 --> 00:22:34.120
Will her fever go down
if we dump water on her?

351
00:22:34.120 --> 00:22:36.210
– You dumbass!
– You dumbass!

352
00:22:36.210 --> 00:22:39.300
This isn't good. The sun's
about to set for today, Vivi.

353
00:22:39.300 --> 00:22:41.210
Yes... You're right.

354
00:22:41.210 --> 00:22:43.720
Let's drop anchor somewhere.

355
00:22:43.720 --> 00:22:46.970
We can't sail at night
without Nami's navigation.

356
00:22:46.970 --> 00:22:47.970
True.

357
00:23:14.920 --> 00:23:17.130
Brr, it's cold...

358
00:23:21.050 --> 00:23:23.720
Almost a full moon, huh?

359
00:23:36.650 --> 00:23:38.440
Brr! Oh, crap, I fell asleep!

360
00:23:40.440 --> 00:23:41.820
You're up early, Usopp!

361
00:23:41.820 --> 00:23:44.240
I can't just sit around doing nothing!

362
00:23:44.240 --> 00:23:47.780
We gotta get out of this jam
as quickly as possible!

363
00:23:47.780 --> 00:23:50.660
Yeah. Good point.

364
00:23:57.290 --> 00:24:02.130
Say, isn't this area
unusually calm and cold?

365
00:24:02.130 --> 00:24:05.470
Yeah, sudden, strange calms...

366
00:24:05.470 --> 00:24:10.100
I guess that's another
erratic quirk of the Grand Line.

367
00:24:10.100 --> 00:24:11.930
That's not necessarily the case.

368
00:24:11.930 --> 00:24:12.560
Huh?

369
00:24:12.930 --> 00:24:15.310
This is likely proof of a nearby island.

370
00:24:15.310 --> 00:24:18.020
Sanji, can you carefully
scan the horizon?

371
00:24:18.480 --> 00:24:19.520
Vivi?

372
00:24:20.730 --> 00:24:23.110
A winter island is nearby.
I'm certain of it.

373
00:24:23.110 --> 00:24:24.610
Winter island?

374
00:24:23.610 --> 00:24:24.610
Ow!

375
00:24:25.280 --> 00:24:30.120
Climate-wise, the Grand Line
has four basic island types:

376
00:24:30.910 --> 00:24:35.250
Summer isles, spring isles,
autumn isles, and winter isles.

377
00:24:35.250 --> 00:24:39.290
In addition, each one generally
has four seasons of its own.

378
00:24:37.870 --> 00:24:49.840
<b>Summer Island Spring Island Autumn Island Winter Island</b>
<b>Summery Summer Wintery Winter</b>

379
00:24:39.420 --> 00:24:44.250
On the Grand Line, you contend
with no fewer than sixteen seasons.

380
00:24:44.250 --> 00:24:49.840
There are summer island summers
and even winter island winters.

381
00:24:50.970 --> 00:24:56.180
Of course, there are many exceptions
and unknown climates.

382
00:24:56.180 --> 00:24:57.680
I get it.

383
00:24:57.680 --> 00:25:01.190
The Grand Line consists
of strings of various islands,

384
00:25:01.190 --> 00:25:05.610
and weather is adversely affected
on the seas between them.

385
00:25:05.610 --> 00:25:06.740
That's right.

386
00:25:06.740 --> 00:25:12.490
So when the weather stabilizes,
you're near an island.

387
00:25:12.990 --> 00:25:15.580
You're right! There it is!

388
00:25:19.000 --> 00:25:21.750
We found an island!

389
00:25:23.290 --> 00:25:24.710
An island?!

390
00:25:24.710 --> 00:25:27.510
Oh! An island! We found an island!

391
00:25:27.510 --> 00:25:31.550
Hey, Nami! Great news!
It's an island! You'll get better!

392
00:25:31.550 --> 00:25:34.180
There's an island! An island! Island!

393
00:25:34.180 --> 00:25:40.020
Island! Island! Island! Island!

394
00:25:40.020 --> 00:25:42.690
Island! Isl...
Just go look already. I'll watch her.

395
00:25:47.150 --> 00:25:49.990
An island!

396
00:25:49.990 --> 00:25:54.280
White! So white! Has to be snow!
A snow island, huh?!

397
00:25:54.280 --> 00:25:58.620
Hey, Luffy! Just remember,
this isn't the time for adventure!

398
00:25:58.620 --> 00:26:00.330
It's a quick stop to find a doctor.

399
00:26:00.330 --> 00:26:02.790
Once Nami's looked at, we're gone!

400
00:26:02.790 --> 00:26:04.670
Hey! Hey, Luffy!

401
00:26:05.290 --> 00:26:08.670
Snow is so nice and white!

402
00:26:08.670 --> 00:26:10.340
It's no use. He's not listening.

403
00:26:10.340 --> 00:26:13.180
H-H-Hold on! Is this a good idea?!

404
00:26:13.180 --> 00:26:16.220
If there's snow, won't there
also be snow monsters?!

405
00:26:16.220 --> 00:26:19.220
And we don't know
if people live there! Oh, no!

406
00:26:19.220 --> 00:26:21.980
My chronic can't-get-on-this-island disease!

407
00:26:21.980 --> 00:26:25.730
Snow! I love snow! It's white!

408
00:26:25.730 --> 00:26:27.610
Guess I'll prep us for landfall.

409
00:26:36.530 --> 00:26:38.160
All this snow!

410
00:26:38.160 --> 00:26:40.160
It's pure happiness!

411
00:26:40.160 --> 00:26:43.500
This is really something.
What's with those mountains?

412
00:26:44.290 --> 00:26:47.920
Say, Luffy. Aren't you cold,
dressed like that?

413
00:26:47.920 --> 00:26:50.170
It's minus 10 degrees right now!

414
00:26:50.170 --> 00:26:52.510
That's when bears
get ready to hibernate!

415
00:26:52.920 --> 00:26:54.760
Huh? Oh.

416
00:26:56.300 --> 00:26:57.390
So cold!

417
00:26:57.390 --> 00:26:59.260
– Took you long enough!
– Took you long enough!

418
00:27:04.190 --> 00:27:06.400
It's a waterfall of melted snow.

419
00:27:06.400 --> 00:27:08.400
We may be able to dock here.

420
00:27:09.070 --> 00:27:12.150
So, who's going doctor hunting?

421
00:27:12.150 --> 00:27:13.570
Actually, you see any people?

422
00:27:14.070 --> 00:27:14.740
I'm going!

423
00:27:14.740 --> 00:27:15.780
So am I!

424
00:27:15.780 --> 00:27:17.200
Okay! Have fun!

425
00:27:17.200 --> 00:27:19.910
That's far enough, pirates!

426
00:27:25.120 --> 00:27:27.170
Hey. I found people.

427
00:27:27.170 --> 00:27:30.420
But... they don't seem too friendly.

428
00:27:31.880 --> 00:27:33.760
Attention, pirates!

429
00:27:33.760 --> 00:27:37.340
Turn around and leave
this place immediately!

430
00:27:37.340 --> 00:27:39.510
We came to find a doctor!

431
00:27:39.510 --> 00:27:41.060
There's a sick person on board!

432
00:27:41.060 --> 00:27:44.520
That's a dirty trick,
you pirate bastards!

433
00:27:44.520 --> 00:27:49.150
On our island, any and all
pirates are barred entry!

434
00:27:49.150 --> 00:27:53.690
Raise anchor and leave,
or we'll blow your ship to smithereens!

435
00:27:55.030 --> 00:27:58.320
They really hate our guts.
And we've only just met.

436
00:27:58.320 --> 00:27:59.530
Less talking!

437
00:27:59.530 --> 00:28:00.490
They're shooting!

438
00:28:00.490 --> 00:28:02.410
You did not just do that!

439
00:28:02.410 --> 00:28:03.540
– No, Sanji!
– Bastard!

440
00:28:14.090 --> 00:28:17.090
Vivi!
